transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling, this is John, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, yes, I just placed an order, and I placed it twice inadvertently.

Speaker 1: I was trying to expedite my shipping.

Speaker 2: Oh, yeah, I can help you.

Speaker 1: I don't care if I get both orders, but I just wanted to make sure I got one coming express.

Speaker 2: I got you. I need your name and zip code.

Speaker 1: What do you need?

Speaker 2: Name and zip code.

Speaker 1: Name and zip code. Robert Conrad at 05674.

Speaker 2: It's 1248 Sugarbush Access Road.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, so one does have the express shipping on it.

Speaker 1: That will go out on Monday for you, but they're not going to send both.

Speaker 2: So do you just want me to cancel one and refund you for it?

Speaker 1: Yeah, if it's going to go out Monday, let's just cancel the express shipping one.

Speaker 2: Okay, okay, I will do that for you.

Speaker 1: So the other one will just go out regular mail on Monday.

Speaker 2: That would be fine.

Speaker 1: Okay, I've gone ahead and taken care of that for you.

Speaker 2: All right, thanks a lot.

Speaker 1: Thanks, sir.

Speaker 2: Have a good night.

Speaker 1: You too, bye-bye.
